The paper deals with steganalysis, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The experiments are conducted on image databases, and the paper uses image features based on Rich Models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves supervised classification, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Wavelet Obtained Weights (WOW), which is a signal processing technique (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of Cover Source Mismatch, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
